title: Cohttp body stream not consumed after streaming LLM response, leaking connections
---
## Summary
After streaming LLM responses, cohttp emits 'Body not consumed, leaking stream!' warnings. This indicates the HTTP response body stream is being abandoned without being drained, causing connection leaks.

## Observed in daemon.log
[16:46:20.232] WARN  Body not consumed, leaking stream! Refer to https://github.com/mirage/ocaml-cohttp/issues/730
[16:48:09.547] WARN  Body not consumed, leaking stream!
Both occurrences follow a LLM streaming call (provider=zai_coding model=glm-5).

## Root Cause (suspected)
src/http_client.ml post_stream (line 100-105): returns the Lwt_stream from Cohttp_lwt.Body.to_stream directly.
If the consumer (process_sse_stream in provider.ml) exits early (e.g., on restart signal, agent cancellation, or exception in on_chunk), the stream is abandoned without being drained.
Cohttp detects the undrained stream and logs the warning.

## Impact
Connection leak per occurrence. Under load or with repeated restarts/errors, this can exhaust the connection pool.

## Fix
Ensure stream is fully consumed or explicitly drained on any exit path from process_sse_stream. Use Lwt.finalize or Lwt.catch to drain remaining chunks on error/cancellation.